summary:
The Security Council,

Welcoming the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations operation in Cyprus, 
Reaffirms all its relevant resolutions on Cyprus, particularly resolution 1251 (1999) and subsequent resolutions;

Decides to extend the mandate of UNFICYP until 15 December 2003;

Endorses the increase of the UNFICYP civilian police component by 34 officers;

Notes limited steps by the Turkish Cypriot side to ease restrictions on UNFICYP, but urges them to rescind all remaining restrictions;

Expresses concern at recent violations by the Turkish Cypriot side and Turkish forces at Strovilia and urges them to restore the prior military status quo;

Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report by 1 December 2003 on the implementation of this resolution;

Decides to remain seized of the matter.
